result.execSummary:
The defendant Elizabeth C. Dolajeck was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

(10:19 AM case called.) Defendant Elizabeth C. Dolajeck appeared by video, in custody in the Taycheedah Correctional Institution. Attorney Roger M Hillestad in court for Elizabeth C. Dolajeck. Prosecuting attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant waives right to a personal appearance and wants to proceed. Court accepts the defendant's waiver to a personal appearance.
Agreement has been reached and is recited by counsel.
Prior offense acknowledged for repeater enhancer.
Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1: Possession of Methamphetamine as a Repeater.
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Court accepts the defendant's No Contest plea and finds the defendant Guilty of Count 1.
State makes a statement regrading sentencing recommendation.
Attorney Hillestad makes a statement regarding sentencing recommendation.
Defendant makes a statement.

Court orders sentence as follows:
1.5 years Initial Confinement followed by 1.5 years Extended Supervision concurrent to any other sentences with the following conditions:
Maintain absolute sobriety. No contact with any known drug dealers/users, except in a therapeutic setting. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge and pay court costs. 65 days sentence credit. Court orders the defendant is eligible for SAP and CIP. Any remaining charges including uncharged DA case #22EC1370 and case 22TR607 are dismissed and read in.
